'''Russ Manning''' ([[January 5]], [[1920s#1929|1929]] &ndash; [[December 1]], [[1981]]) was the writer and penciller of numerous [[Star Wars (comic strip)|''Star Wars'' black-and-white newspaper comic strips]] published in [[1979]] and [[1980]]. His works were later colorized and re-released by [[Dark Horse Comics]] in the ''[[Classic Star Wars: The Early Adventures]]'' series.

In [[1960s#1963|1963]], he created ''Magnus Robot Fighter'', which continued in reprints throughout the 1970s.

